result.execSummary:
The defendant Dante Eglace Jenkins Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dante Eglace Jenkins Jr is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dante Eglace Jenkins Jr was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct - Domestic Abuse Repeater [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Domestic Abuse Repeater], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Dante Eglace Jenkins Jr was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dante Eglace Jenkins in court with attorney Eric Daniel Lowenberg.  Defendant Dante Eglace Jenkins in custody.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court ordered defendant to serve 12 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 301 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for treatment.
AS TO COUNT 3:
The Court ordered defendant to serve 7 months in the House of Correction, consecutive to count 2, with credit for zero days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for treatment.

Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and fees by 12/8/17, or to be docketed as a civil judgment.

Defendant Dante Eglace Jenkins in court with attorney Eric Daniel Lowenberg.  Defendant Dante Eglace Jenkins in custody.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties have reached a resolution in this matter.  Pursuant to negotiations counts 1 and 4 are ordered dismissed.
AS to count 2 REPEATER enhancer is deleted.  AS to count 3 Domestic Abuse Repeater and REPEATER enhancer are deleted.
AS to counts 2 and 3:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead NO CONTEST.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.
Defense counsel is requesting that defendant's bail be modified to a PR BOND pending sentencing.  Court denies motion.  Defendant is remanded pending sentencing on 12-8-2015.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for December 8, 2015 at 08:15 am.
